solutions.content:
You can refer to other posts for basic 3D DP solution. Here I optimize the 3D DP with two tricks:

* Early return if the length of path is odd
* Use `bitset` with each bit representing a possible number of open parenthesis. When we meet a new opening `'('`, we should add one more open parenthesis to all previous memorized result. With `bitset` we simply left shift. Similarly, For `')'` we right shift.

```
bool hasValidPath(vector<vector<char>>& grid) {
    int m = grid.size(), n = grid[0].size();
    if ((m + n - 1) % 2) // early return for odd length path
        return false;
    vector<bitset<100>> dp(n + 1);
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        dp[0][0] = !i;
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
            dp[j + 1] = grid[i][j] == '(' ? (dp[j] | dp[j + 1]) << 1: (dp[j] | dp[j + 1]) >> 1;
    }
    return dp[n][0];
}
```

