solutions.content:
### Explanation:
* `k` denotes the running sum of the parentheses. For each `(`, add +1 for each `)` add -1
* At any point `k` should not be less than 0 else valid parentheses beyond that point is not possible
*  If `(A[i][j] == ')' and k < 1)` k will become < 0 when we perform k - 1, so we return `False`
*  `if i == m - 1 and j == n - 1: return A[i][j] == ')' and k == 1` If we are on the last cell return `True` if last cell contains `)` and `k == 1`. `k - 1` will be `= 0` which will mean parentheses are balanced. For every other case on last cell, we return `False` 
*  The `any()` function returns True if any item in an iterable are true, otherwise it returns False.

```
def hasValidPath(self, A: List[List[str]]) -> bool:
	@cache
	def dfs(i, j, k):
		if i >= len(A) or j >= len(A[0]) or (A[i][j] == ')' and k < 1): return False
		if i == len(A) - 1 and j == len(A[0]) - 1: return A[i][j] == ')' and k == 1
		return any(dfs(i + x, j + y, k + (1 if A[i][j] == '(' else -1)) for x, y in [[0, 1], [1, 0]])
	return dfs(0, 0, 0)
```
Time complexity: O(mn(m+n))

