solutions.content:
At dp[i][j] we count how many excess open parenthesis we have till ```i,j``` (>= 0, negative means that particular path can be ignored from now on).  Now, at ```i,j``` if it's open, we increase all counts by 1 (i.e left-shift) otherwise decrease all counts by 1.  
C++ bitset<201> can simulate this directly. increase can be left-shift etc.
```
typedef bitset<201> sp;
typedef vector<sp> vsp;
typedef vector<vsp> vvsp;
class Solution {
public:
    bool hasValidPath(vector<vector<char>>& grid) {
        int m = grid.size(), n = grid[0].size();
        vvsp dp = vvsp(m, vsp(n, sp()));
        dp[0][0] = grid[0][0] == '(';
        for (int i=0;i<m;++i) for (int j=0;j<n;++j) {
            dp[i][j] = dp[i][j] | (j ? dp[i][j-1] : 0) | (i ? dp[i-1][j] : 0 );
            if (grid[i][j] == '(') dp[i][j] <<= 1;
            else dp[i][j] >>= 1;
        }
        return dp.back().back().test(0) > 0;
    }
};
```

