we can solve this question easily by taking '(' as +1 and ')' as -1.Now start adding the cell values in right or down direction and if sum is negative that means it cant be a valid path as it can not be balanced at any condition.
Now do a recursion and check if we have already visited this node with th current sum, if yes then return the memoized value otherwise go to the right and down and return OR of both paths.
Base condition: if we will reach at the bottom right cell then sum should be 0 for a correct path otherwise the paranthesis must be unbalanced.

PFB my code for your reference:)

