solutions.content:
Simple Intution ,It is same as to find the Path from top left corner to right down corner but here the catch is to find the valid path which should statisfy the given conditions like **()** (parentheses)

And there is a condition we should take care 
1. The Path should not start with **)**. 
2. The path should not end with **(**.

**DP Approach**
* First take a variable lets say **start**  which will count the parentheses i.e if "**(**" then start++  if "**)**" start--.
* Traverse the all possible paths with right and down.
* Until it statisfy the condition i.e (n-1,m-1 and start=0)
* if the start is 0 at the end that means we got a path with equal no of parentheses.
* To Optimize the code Use Memomization.

```
class Solution {
    Boolean dp[][][];
    public boolean hasValidPath(char[][] grid) 
    {
        dp=new Boolean[grid.length][grid[0].length][grid.length+grid[0].length];
        return helper(grid,0,0,0);
    }
    public boolean helper(char[][] grid,int i,int j,int start)
    {
        if(i>=grid.length || j>=grid[0].length) return false;
        if(grid[i][j]=='(')
            start++;
        else
            start--;
        if(start<0) return false;
        if(i==grid.length-1 && j==grid[0].length-1) return start==0;
        if(dp[i][j][start]!=null) return dp[i][j][start];
        dp[i][j][start]=(helper(grid,i+1,j,start) || helper(grid,i,j+1,start));
        return dp[i][j][start];
    }
}
```

