**Intuition**
For any given cell (x,y), it is possible to have a valid string starting from (0,0) only if number of open brackets upto (x,y) are 0. A path is invalid if number of ')' exceeds number of '('. 

**Approach**
For each cell (i,j) of dp array, maintain a hashset and store the number of open brackets, updating the values in the hashset from dp[i-1][j] and dp[i][j-1].
if current character is '(', then increment the values from hashsets of dp[i-1][j] and dp[i][j-1].
if current character is ')', thendecrement the values from hashsets of dp[i-1][j] and dp[i][j-1], ignoring negative values.
True is returned only if hashset of last cell has 0.
**Code**
```
class Solution {
    class hs{
        HashSet<Integer> s;
        public hs(){
            s = new HashSet<>();
        }

    }
    public boolean hasValidPath(char[][] grid) {
        int n = grid.length;
        int m = grid[0].length;
        hs[][] dp = new hs[n][m];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                dp[i][j] = new hs();
            }
        }
        dp[0][0].s.add(1);
        for(int i=1;i<m;i++){
            int k = (grid[0][i]=='('?1:-1);
            for(int x: dp[0][i-1].s){
                if(x+k<0){
                    continue;
                }
                dp[0][i].s.add(x+k);

            }
        }

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            int k = (grid[i][0]=='('?1:-1);

            for(int x: dp[i-1][0].s){
                if(x+k<0){
                    continue;
                }
                dp[i][0].s.add(x+k);

            }
        }

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<m;j++){
               int k = (grid[i][j]=='('?1:-1);
                for(int x: dp[i-1][j].s){
                    if(x+k<0){
                        continue;
                    }
                    dp[i][j].s.add(x+k);
                }
                for(int x: dp[i][j-1].s){
                    if(x+k<0){
                        continue;
                    }
                    dp[i][j].s.add(x+k);
                    }

            }
        }


        return dp[n-1][m-1].s.contains(0);
    }
}
```

