solutions.content:
**Hello guys,**
this is a very simple explanation for `Minimum Obstacle Removal to Reach Corner` problem.

insert a[0][0] in multiset initially
now get ms.begin(), it will give shortest distance path till now,
`pair<int,pair<int,int>>p=*ms.begin();`
`int x=p.second.first, y=p.second.second;` // current node's position

let check for further path in all possible 4 directions means means (x-1,y), (x+1,y), (x,y-1) & (x,y+1)
and check if neighbour nodes are unvisited and theirs distance are greater `dis[x][y]+a[x][y]`

**Here** `dis[x][y]` gives minimum number of Obstacle removal to reach (i,j)

**for eg.**
we are checking node (x-1,y) then,
```
if(x-1>=0 && vis[x-1][y]==0) { 
	if(dis[x-1][y]>dis[x][y]+a[x][y]) // check if dis is greater
	{
		dis[x-1][y]=dis[x][y]+a[x][y]; // update distance
		ms.insert({dis[x-1][y], {x-1,y}});
	}
}
```
we get minimum number of Obstacle removal count in `dis[n-1][m-1]`

**Code:**

```
#define pb push_back
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumObstacles(vector<vector<int>>& a) {

        int n=a.size(), m=a[0].size();
        int node=n*m;

        int vis[n+1][m+1];
        memset(vis, 0, sizeof(vis));

        int dis[n+1][m+1];
        for(int i=0;i<=n;++i) for(int j=0;j<=m;++j) dis[i][j]=1e7;
        dis[0][0]=a[0][0];

        multiset<pair<int,pair<int,int>>>ms;
        ms.insert({dis[0][0],{0,0}});

        while(ms.size())
        {
            pair<int,pair<int,int>>p=*ms.begin();
            ms.erase(ms.begin());

            int d=p.first;
            int x=p.second.first, y=p.second.second;
            if(vis[x][y]) continue;
            vis[x][y]=1;

            if(x-1>=0 && vis[x-1][y]==0) {
                if(dis[x-1][y]>dis[x][y]+a[x][y])
