Just run a greedy BFS, Starting from cell `(0,0)` , push any unvisited adjacent empty cell to the front of the queue  and the unvisited wall cells to the back of the queue (We prefer paths with the most number of empty cells, pushing empty cells to the front of the queue ensure all the nearby empty cells would be visited first because they all have the same total weight as the current cell , when we have no empty cells that can be visited left, we will move to the nearest wall cells to continue exploring other possible paths.

