solutions.content:
**Using Unordered map and set**
In this method, we use unordered map with *key* as *char* and value as an *unordered_set*. For each prefix character, we insert its remaining suffix string in its value set. Now, for every character, we find the common suffixes with every other character. We wont be able to swap the characters having the same suffixes. 
For ex. 
```
		ideas = ["coffee","cone","chips","time","toffee"]
		c    -> ["offee","one","hips"]
		t    -> ["offee","ime"]
```
Now, the common suffix in `'c'` and` 't'` is `offee`, thus we cant make a name with it, but we can make a valid name with the remaining suffixes. 
Thus, total valid names will be (2x1)x2 = 4

**This method is a bit costly with space and time**

```
class Solution {
public:
    long long distinctNames(vector<string>& ideas) {
        unordered_map <char,unordered_set<string>> mp;
        for(auto u : ideas) mp[u[0]].insert(u.substr(1,u.size()-1));

        long long ans = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i<26; i++){
            for(int j = i+1; j<26; j++){
                unordered_set <string> s1 = mp[i+'a'], s2 = mp[j+'a'];

                int comm = 0;
                for(auto u : s1)
                    if(s2.find(u)!=s2.end()) comm++;

                ans += (long long)(s1.size()-comm)*(long long)(s2.size()-comm)*2;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
****
****
**Using 2d array**
This method does not uses any *unordered_set* as value of *unordered_map*, instead, we use a 2d array to store if we could swap two characters or not. 
`dp[i][j] = 1`, tells us that we can swap i<sup>th</sup> character with j<sup>th</sup> character. 
For ex,
```
		ideas = ["coffee","cone","chips","time","toffee"]
		c    -> ["offee","one","hips"]
		t    -> ["offee","ime"]
```
We iterate over ideas, and try swapping first character of each element with every character and check if the new character is already in ideas or not. If it is not present in ideas, we increment `dp[original_char][swapped_char]`.
We add `dp[i][j]*dp[j][i] `to our answer, that ensure that answer is incremented only when` i->j` and` j->i`, both are valid swappings.  

```
class Solution {
public:
    long long distinctNames(vector<string>& ideas) {
        unordered_map <string,int> mp;
        for(auto u : ideas) mp[u]++;

        vector <vector <int>> dp(26,vector<int>(26,0));
        for(int i = 0; i<ideas.size(); i++){
            string temp = ideas[i];
            char ch1 = temp[0];
            for(int j = 0; j<26; j++){
                temp[0] = j+'a';
                if(mp.find(temp)==mp.end()) 
                    dp[ch1-'a'][j]++;
            }
        }

        long long ans = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i<26; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j<26; j++){
                ans += dp[i][j]*dp[j][i];
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

