# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
**Idea :** 
- Brute force is easy  for all the pairs  check for those which are present in our vector are invlaid else valid so it can be simply done by using two loops but will be O(n^2)  so tle.
- Optimal can be done by some how eliminatig the repetition we are doing i.e we know there are only 26 letters that  a word  can start  from and we know if first letter of two strings are same they will be still the same after swaping so we don't need them for our company name i.e they are invalid and  also if two strings having first letter different and rest  same they also cant be used because swapping them will result in two strings which are present already e.g coffee and toffee  swap c and t --> toffee and coffee so again they become one another so these are the two things where we are doing repetiton while they are not giving us some answer so if we make groups on the basis of first letter and check if suffix part is differnt of two groups they will be counted else not .

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Algo:
- Take a set or map of 26 size which will store groups of strings where a group is based on first letter and we will store only suffix part . Set will automatically eleimate duolicates (so one thing is gone).
- Then we know only 26 letters are there so using two loops of size 25 X 26 just like doing brute force n*n we will check for a group i if it contains group j's suffix strings or not if not count them  and vice-versa for i in j . 
- Then no.of ditinct grouping = ci*cj *2 (2 is beacuse e.g `xah` `oor `and `oor` `xah` both can used as company names so mutually 2 times )
# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n*m*25*26)$$ where n=ideas.size and m= ideas[i].size
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(N*26)$$ N=no.of strings in ideas vector
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
**Brute Force**
```
#define ll long long 
    long long distinctNames(vector<string>& ideas) {
        map<string,int>mp;
        int c=0,n=ideas.size();
        for(auto s:ideas)mp[s]++;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                string s1=ideas[i],s2=ideas[j];
                swap(s1[0],s2[0]);
                if(mp[s1] or mp[s2]);
                else c++;
            }
        }
        return c;
    }
