## Complexity analysis:
---
#### Time complexity:

Let's say we have `n` words (sounds sus) in the given array `ideas`. We loop through the array to populate our hashmap costing an $$O(n)$$.

Then we iterate over the keyset of the map which stores characters. At max there can be $$26$$ characters. We has a nested for loop again inside it traversing the keyset. So we have a $$O(26^2)$$ so far.

Inside the previous loop, we iterate over the set which contains the suffices of the characters that can be $$n$$ at max.

So this makes up a $$O(26^2 * n)$$

Therefore total **Time complexity**: $$O(n + 26^2*n)$$

---
#### Space complexity:
We can have at max $$26$$ characters in the keyset and each of them can have $$n$$ suffices mapped to them.

Therefore **Space complexity**: $$O(26*n) => O(n)$$

---

