# Intuition
For every idea in ideas, we need to find out no. of other ideas, which can be combined with it.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Any current idea will accept other idea, if we take other idea's starting character and replace it into the starting character of current idea and that doesn't exist in the original array.

So for a match, both, current idea and the other idea, will have to accept each other.

Algo:

First we store all the elements in a map.

Then for each element we check its starting character and characters it accepts(ie. starting characters of other ideas which it can combine with).

Then in the third iteration for each idea, we fetch the count of elements, which accept the current element and start with character which the current element accepts.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long distinctNames(vector<string>& ideas) {

        int n = ideas.size();

        unordered_map<string,int> m;
        for(string idea:ideas){
            m[idea]++;
        }

        vector<vector<int>> starts_accepts(26,vector<int>(26));
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            string str = ideas[i];
            int starts = ideas[i][0]-'a';

            for(char c='a';c<='z';c++){
                str[0] = c;
                if(m.find(str)==m.end()){
                    int accepts = str[0]-'a';
                    starts_accepts[starts][accepts]++;
                }
            }
        }

        long long ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            string str = ideas[i];
            int starts = ideas[i][0]-'a';

            for(char c='a';c<='z';c++){
                str[0] = c;
                if(m.find(str)==m.end()){
                    int accepts = str[0]-'a';
                    ans = ans+starts_accepts[accepts][starts];
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;

    }
};
```

