so we need pairs of words which are after swapping their first character, not present in the original list. 
I precalculated the thing that if we swap letter let say 'a' to 'c' then what are the number of such words starting with 'a' which after swapping  with 'c' doesn't exist in original list.
let call this sum v[a][c]  
now v[c][a]  will denote that how many words are there with c which on swapping with a , are not present in list.
so we can use v[a][c]  and v[c][a] to form pairs 
total possible pairs = v[a][c] * v[c][a]


