1. First iterate through the ideas and store in unordered_map (easy access).
2. create vector of 26x26 or 2-d array
3. now go over each element of ideas. for each element extract the suffix. Now the prefix (first character can be anything from a to z)
4. There are some constraints to step3. First if this new character index is same as previous character index then there is actually no new word forming, just continue.
5. now after adding all alphabets (except prefixIndex char) to suffix, check if it is present in map or not. If it is present then it means it is one of the idea that shares same suffix. hence just continue.
6. now t[prefixIndex][j] += 1 indicates that prefixIndex character can be replaced by jth character. 
7. now iterate through the 2-d array and check for positions (i,j) which are greater than zero.
8. now here is the biggest catch. WHY ADD "(t[i][j]*t[j][i])"?
9. t[i][j] indicates that j can replace i. t[j][i] indicates that i can replace j. if both can replace each other then it means both i and j were present as prefix in ideas array. 
10. lets say we have "abc", "mxy" then (t[a][m]>0 && t[m][a]>0) , (t[a][c]>0 but t[c][a]==0). hence overall we will get some +ve value in t[a][m] case and 0 in t[a][c] case. 
