# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Brute Force : Check for every pair of words that will be O(n^2)
Optimised : Group the words on the basis of first character of every word
After grouping iteration will be O(group * group) that can be considered and O(26*26) as per constraint

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public long distinctNames(String[] ideas) {
        //grouping the words of ideas array on the basis of first character
        Map<Character, Set<String>> map = new HashMap<>();
        //As we crerating group on the basis of first character, I can store all the words in the grop without first character
        //to handle the same suffix scenario
        for(String idea : ideas){
            char c = idea.charAt(0);
            if(!map.containsKey(c))
                map.put(c, new HashSet<>());
            map.get(c).add(idea.substring(1,idea.length()));
        }
        // System.out.println(map);
        long result = 0;

        //now for every group check the suffixes of group 1 with iterative group2 if common suffixes maintain a count of it
        //non common suffixes can concatinate and make valid words

        for(Map.Entry<Character, Set<String>> key1 : map.entrySet()){
            Set<String> group1 = key1.getValue();
            for(Map.Entry<Character, Set<String>> key2 : map.entrySet()){
                if(key1 == key2)
                    continue;
                int commonSuffixes = 0;
                Set<String> group2 = key2.getValue();
                for(String suffix : group1){
                    if(group2.contains(suffix))
                        commonSuffixes++;
                }

                int validSuffixes1 = group1.size() - commonSuffixes;
                int validSuffixes2 = group2.size() - commonSuffixes;

                result += (validSuffixes1 * validSuffixes2);
            }
        }   

        return result;

    }
}
```

