can I eliminate some cases so that we don't have to search for all combinations???
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The main idea is to eliminate some comparisions.

We can make an array of set of size 26 where we can store strings according to theri first characte.

If two strings start with the same character then, swapping their first characters doesn't makes sense.

Also if the strings have first character different and remaining characters same doesn't makes sense.
Ex: coffee and toffee ----> toffee and coffee
If we change the first characters then it again makes the same word.

Also if we find a pair that follows the conditions then the reverse of the pair also satisfies the conditions.
Ex: cash and pet  ----> pash cet
    pet and cash  ----> cet pash


So, if we are able to find one such pair then we will multiply it with '2'.

