![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/b5c4b00f-e239-42cb-8c71-5893de846e8a_1655201037.4433916.png)

**Input :** `["cat","cake","rat","make","roll","can","ran"]`
**Output :** 8

Eliminate common elements from any **2 sets** (suppose `a` and `b`) and make pairs from 
remaining elements same as cartesian product of two sets.
**valid pairs** = `ans += (a.size()-common)*(b.size()-common)`

  c --> <ins>at</ins>, <ins>an</ins>, ake
  r --> <ins>at</ins>, oll, <ins>an</ins>
 m --> <ins>ake</ins>

----
**Time complexity :** `O(26*26*N)`
**Space complexity :** `O(26*N)` 

----
```
class Solution {
public:

    long long distinctNames(vector<string>& ideas) {

        int n=ideas.size();
        long long ans=0;;
        unordered_map<char,unordered_set<string>>mp;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(ideas[i].size()!=1)
                mp[ideas[i][0]].insert(ideas[i].substr(1)); // t --> offee, ime, c --> offee, d --> onuts
            else                                            // pair of ideas from the same group is invalid.
                mp[ideas[i][0]].insert(ideas[0]);
        }

        // pairs of ideas from different groups
        for(auto i = mp.begin(); i!=mp.end();i++) // --> O(26)
        {
            auto k = i;
            k++;
            for(auto j = k;j!=mp.end();j++){

                // two sets (i->second and j->second)
                int common=0;
                for(auto &s1 : i->second){
                    if(j->second.count(s1) > 0){
                        common++;
                    }
                }
                // valid pairs
                ans += (i->second.size()-common)*(j->second.size()-common);

            }
        }
        return ans*2;        // final answer multiplied by 2 because we can use single valid pair 2 times for 
		                     // the naming of company.
    }
};
```
