solutions.content:
**INTUITION**

Any word starting with letter `i` which can change it's first letter to `j`, can be paired with all the words starting with letter `j` which can change their first letter to `i`

Here, `cnt[i][j] = number of words starting with letter 'i' that can change their first letter to 'j' `

**CODE**

```
long long distinctNames(vector<string>& ideas) {
	unordered_set<string> s(ideas.begin(), ideas.end());
	vector<vector<long long>> cnt(26, vector<long long>(26, 0LL));

	for(auto &x : ideas) {
		string curr = x;
		for(int j = 0; j<26; j++) {
			curr[0] = 'a' + j;
			if(!s.count(curr)) cnt[x[0]-'a'][j]++;
		}
	}

	long long res = 0LL;
	for(auto &x : ideas) {
		string curr = x;
		for(int i = 0; i<26; i++) {
			curr[0] = 'a' + i;
			// If current word can change it's letter to 'j' we can pair it with all the words than can change their first letters to x[0]-'a'
			if(!s.count(curr)) res += cnt[i][x[0]-'a'];
		}
	}

	return res;
}
```

**TIME COMPLEXITY**

We only run a loop over all the words twice, followed by a loop of 26 characters which can be ignored. So the final complexity of this solution is `O(n)`.

