solutions.content:
**Concept- If we XOR odd number of ones then we
get 1 and if we XOR even number of ones then
we will get 0.**
**1^1^1^.....^1(odd number of times)=1
1^1^1^.....^1(even number of times)=0**
**Steps-**
* Each number has bits when we convert it into
binary. Eg. 4 has 3 bits which are 100.
So First we will find the maximum number of bits
from numbers present in nums.
* Count zeroes and ones at each bit position.
* If bits are the number of bits then we iterate at each bit
position and check if it ones are odd at this 
position, if it is then we will store one 
and if it is not then is ones are not zero then
we can get 1 as we can convert a 1 to 0 not 0
to 1 because of AND opertion.
* Calculate the answer.


**Better Understaing**
**Eg.
nums:[3,2,4,6]
WRITING BITS FOR EACH NUMBER-**
**3-011
2-010
4-100
6-110**

THERE ARE 3 BITS LETS WRITE THE NUMBER OF ONES AND ZEROES FOR EACH POSITION.
Ones-[2,3,1]
Zeroes-[2,1,3]
At index 2, there are 1 ones which is odd so we can get one at this bit position. Similarly for 
index 1, ones are odd, but for index 0 ones are even which is 2. In what condition we can get 
one at this bits position? We have to make a 1 to 0 or a zero to 1 to convert ones to odd.
If we convert a 0 to 1 it will not work because when we AND with the same number it will 
again yield a zero at this position. So we will convert a 1 to 0 so make ones odd. It is only 
possible when count of ones are not zero.
I hope you got it!!



```
class Solution {
public:
    int maximumXOR(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        int num=nums[n-1]; //maximum number of bits will be present in the largest number
        int bits=0; //counting the bits for the maximum  number of bits among all the numbers
        while(num>0){
            num=num>>1;
            bits++;
        }
        vector<int> ones(bits,0), zeroes(bits,0); //ones will store number of ones at this bit position in every number
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            num=nums[i];
            int idx=0;
            while(num>0){
                int bit=num&1;//checking current bit is 1 or 0
                if(bit){
                    ones[idx]++;
                }else{
                    zeroes[idx]++;
                }
                num=num>>1;
                idx++;
            }


            //if idx is less then maximum number of bits then increasing the zeroes for those position
            while(idx<bits){
                zeroes[idx]++;
                idx++;
            }
        }


        //If number of ones is odd then we can get 1 bit at this position or if one is even then count of ones at this position must not be zero otherwise this position we will put 0
        vector<int> v;
        for(int i=0;i<bits;i++){
            if(ones[i]%2!=0){
                v.push_back(1);
            }else if(ones[i]>0){
                v.push_back(1);
            }else{
                v.push_back(0);
            }
        }

        //Calculating the final answer
        int res=0;
        for(int i=0;i<bits;i++){
            res=res+pow(2,i)*v[i];
        }


        return res;
    }
};


```

