🔥Approach:-
* Whenever we are doing nums[i] = nums[i] & (nums[i] ^ x). Please note that the And operation will produce the result 0 if any bit of the number is zero.
* It can produce 1/0 depending on the result of nums[i]^x. Because XOR operator can produce 1/0 depending on the x.
* Whenever we XOR all the numbers at the end. If at any bit we have a minimum of one 1 from all the numbers It means that bit can be converted to 1.
