Explanation 
We can unset or set any bit in A[i] by doing A[i]^x. As we can take same or reverse of that bit in x to unset or set the bit.
But in every operation, we also have to do AND with A[i] so we can't set any new bit in the result of one operation.
But still we can unset any bit in any A[i] with one operation.
