# Approach
```
nums[i] & (nums[i] ^ x) = (nums[i] & nums[i]) ^ (nums[i] & x) 
= nums[i] ^ (nums[i] & x);
```
We can do this infinitly, so our xor sum can contain any additional 
```
(nums[i] & x)
```
The thing is that we can add any non-zero bit from nums[i] to xor sum by using this operation. 
Xor sum can be maximized by increasing evenly counted bits to make them odd.

So, the answer would contain every non-zero bit of all nums.
