# Approach
Since `nums[i]` <= $$10^8$$, at most 30 bits, we can check for every bits of every `nums[i]`
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
  int maximumXOR(vector<int>& nums) {
    int result = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < 30; i++) {
      int ones = 0;
      for (const int& num : nums) {
        if (num & (1 << i))
          ones++;
      }
      if (ones % 2 or ones >= 2)
        result |= 1 << i;
    }
    return result;
  }
};
```

**Alternative solution**
- Just take the *OR* of `nums`
```
class Solution {
public:
  int maximumXOR(vector<int>& nums) {
    int result = 0;
    for (const int& num : nums) {
      result |= num;
    }
    return result;
  }
};
```
```
class Solution {
public:
  int maximumXOR(vector<int>& nums) {
    return accumulate(nums.begin(), nums.end(), 0, bit_or<>());
  }
};
```

