nums = [ 3, 2, 4, 6 ]
3 = 0011
2 = 0010
4 = 0100
6 = 0110
XOR(3, 2, 4, 6) = 0011

we have zero 1s at index 0 -> XOR of all bits at index 0 becomes 0
we have two 1s at index 1 -> XOR of all bits at index 1 becomes 0
we have three 1s at index 2 -> XOR of all bits at index 2 becomes 1
we have one 1s at index 3 -> XOR of all bits at index 3 becomes 1
...
we have Odd 1s at index i -> XOR of all bits at index i becomes 1 (good)
we have Even 1s at index i -> XOR of all bits at index i becomes 0 (not good)
```
